<title>JAPAN: Japan May domestic vehicle sales down 9.4% yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Japan May domestic vehicle sales down 9.4% yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-06-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's domestic vehicle sales fell 9.4 percent in May from a year earlier to 319,940 units, the Japan Automobile Dealers Association (JADA) said on Monday.</p>
<p>It was the second year-on-year decline in a row.  </p>
<p>The May sales breakdown was as follows (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p> Total cars		210,634  down 10.6 percent</p>
<p> - Cars over 2001 cc    45,647  down 20.3 percent</p>
<p> - Cars under 2000 cc  164,987  down  7.5 percent</p>
<p> Trucks		    108,513  down  6.9 percent</p>
<p> - Heavy trucks	    9,822  down 11.6 percent</p>
<p> - Light trucks	   98,691  down  6.4 percent</p>
<p> Buses			   793  down 24.6 percent</p>
<p>May sales included 22,921 imported vehicles, down 27.0 percent from the year before.</p>
<p>May vehicle sales by five major Japanese car makers were as follows (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p> Toyota Motor     126,996  down  8.1 percent</p>
<p> Nissan Motor	59,361  down 12.4 percent</p>
<p> Honda Motor	 34,762  down 14.8 percent</p>
<p> Mitsubishi Motors 25,549  down 10.6 percent</p>
<p> Mazda Motor	 20,539  up   12.7 percent</p>
